<DOC><DOCNO> AP880502-0083 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-02-88 1043EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u a PM-HostagesTaken     05-02 0160</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Hostages Taken,0163</SECOND><HEAD>Man Takes Hostages at ATandamp;T Building</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Retransmitting a0559 to CORRECT cycle designation.</NOTE><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man believed to be carrying a hand grenade anda .38-caliber handgun held at least 10 people hostage today on the25th floor of the ATandamp;T building in lower Manhattan, police said.   The incident began shortly before 9:30 a.m. at 22 Cortlandt St.An initial report on the police radio said the man's wife worked onthat floor and he was having some difficulties.   The name of the hostage-taker was not known.   At first, the man was reported to be holding 15 people hostage.After about 30 minutes, he let five people go, according to Lt.Thomas Fahey, a police spokesman.   Police sealed off the block, creating massive traffic jams inthe surrounding streets. The police hostage negotiating team set upoperations on the same floor as the hostage and was in contact withthe man, police said.</TEXT></DOC>